#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:105
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to uniquely identify sampling events"
msgstr "如何唯一識別調查活動"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:109
msgid "Each event is uniquely identified using dwc:eventID and occasionally dwc:parentEventID. Although the type and format of identifier is arbitrary we recommend that publishers choose persistent globally unique identifier.  In the absence of a GUID, publishers may reuse the original fieldNumber."
msgstr "每個活動透過 dwc:eventID 唯一識別，有時也會使用 dwc:parentEventID。雖然標識符的類型和格式是任意的，但建議發布者選擇持久的全域唯一識別碼。如果沒有 GUID，發布者可以重複使用原始的 fieldNumber。"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:111
msgid "Make sure to reuse existing stable identifiers and do not create a new identifier for an event when one is already declared."
msgstr "請確保重用現有的穩定標識符，當活動已有標識符時，請勿重新創建新標識符。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:112
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to capture hierarchy of events"
msgstr "如何掌握調查活動的層次結構"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:115
msgid "Sampling events can be related to each other (e.g., nested samples) via a common parent identifier. For example, several sub-sampling events within a Whittaker Plot each with their own eventID (e.g., “A1:1”, “A1:2”) would share a common parentEventID (e.g., “A1”) thus enabling them to be linked together easily (see Table 4 and Figure 3)."
msgstr "調查活動之間可以相互關聯（例如，巢狀樣本）並共享一個共同的父標識符。例如，某 Whittaker 採樣地中的幾個子調查活動，各自擁有自己的 eventID（例如：“A1:1”、“A1:2”），可共享一個共同的 parentEventID（例如：“A1”），從而使它們能夠相互連結（見表4和圖3）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:117
msgid "Further information on the nature of the relationship (e.g. part of a monitoring series) can be described in the project section of the accompanying metadata."
msgstr "更多關係性資訊（例如屬於某監測系列）可以在附加詮釋資料的專案部分中描述。"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:119
msgid "You may also refer to the following xref:sampling-event-data.adoc#q-how-do-i-publish-a-hierarchy-of-events-recursive-data-type-using-parentEventID[FAQ]."
msgstr "您也可以參考 xref:sampling-event-data.adoc#q-how-do-i-publish-a-hierarchy-of-events-recursive-data-type-using-parentEventID[常見問題]。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:120
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to capture absence data"
msgstr "如何找出缺失資料"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:123
msgid "Refer to the following xref:sampling-event-data.adoc#q-how-do-i-publish-absence-data[FAQ]."
msgstr "請參考 xref:sampling-event-data.adoc#q-how-do-i-publish-absence-data[常見問題]。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:124
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to include supplementary multimedia"
msgstr "如何添加補充多媒體資料"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:127
msgid "You may choose to include supplementary media in order to make the data easier to interpret. For example for vegetation data, it is helpful to include a link to the original scanned relevé sheet when interpreting the data."
msgstr "您可以選擇添加補充媒體資料，以便資料更容易被詮釋。例如，對於植被資料，包含原始掃描的樣區紀錄表連結有助於資料的解讀。"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:129
msgid "The files associated have to be hosted on an external server and linked to the occurrence through the dwc:associatedMedia and dwc:associatedReferences. These files may be images, texts or a combination of both as long as the format type is specified. JPG, PNG, etc. images will be visible as thumbnails while PDFs will appear as clickable links."
msgstr "相關的檔案需要託管在外部伺服器上，並透過 dwc:associatedMedia 和 dwc:associatedReferences 連結到物種出現紀錄。這些檔案可以是圖片、文字，或兩者的組合，只要指定格式類型即可。例如，JPG、PNG 等圖片將以縮圖顯示，而 PDF 將顯示為可點擊的連結。"

#. type: Title ==
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:130
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "Publishing sampling-event data"
msgstr "發布調查活動資料"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:132
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using GUIDs for identifiers"
msgstr "使用 GUID 作為識別碼"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:135
msgid "A number of fields require the usage of unique identifiers: dwc:occurrenceID, dwc:eventID, dwc:organismID and dwc:locationID."
msgstr "以下多個欄位需要使用唯一識別碼：dwc:occurrenceID、dwc:eventID、dwc:organismID 和 dwc:locationID。"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:137
msgid "As mentioned previously, although no particular format is enforced, we advise publishers to use Global Unique IDentifiers (GUIDs). There are a few online services which can provide such identifiers. For example, it is possible to use http://www.geonames.org/ to find (or even generate new) identifiers for dwc:locationID, e.g. http://sws.geonames.org/10793757/ is a GUID for a lake in Greenland."
msgstr "如前所述，雖然沒有強制要求特定格式，但建議發布者使用全域唯一識別碼 (GUID)。一些線上服務可以提供此類識別碼。例如，您可以使用 http://www.geonames.org/ 來查找（甚至生成新的）dwc:locationID 識別碼，例如：http://sws.geonames.org/10793757/ 是格陵蘭一座湖泊的 GUID。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "Protect location of sensitive species"
msgstr "保護敏感物種的位置"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:141
msgid "If your dataset contains sensitive species, there are several ways to handle it:"
msgstr "如果資料集中包含敏感物種，有以下幾種處理方式："

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:143
msgid "Simply removing these species from the dataset,"
msgstr "將這些物種從資料集中移除；"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:144
msgid "Publishing the species identifications at Genus level only,"
msgstr "僅發布到屬級的物種鑑定結果；"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:145
msgid "Publishing the sensitive/protected species in a separate dataset,"
msgstr "將敏感/受保護的物種發布為單獨的資料集；"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:146
msgid "Publish obfuscated sensitive data points in the main dataset and publish non-obfuscated details in an access-limited separate dataset, both datasets including all data records."
msgstr "在主資料集中發布模糊化的敏感資料點，並在一個存取受限的獨立資料集中發布未模糊化的詳細資訊，兩個資料集都應包括完整的資料紀錄。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:147
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preserving verbatim data"
msgstr "保留原始資料"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:150
msgid "Although verbatim data and descriptions are not visible on the GBIF.org web interface, they are made available to the community through downloads. When entering verbatim description, make sure to link them to the original event or occurrence. For example, the ID or code given to the original event should be entered into dwc:fieldNumber; the ID or code given to the original occurrence observation should be entered into dwc:recordNumber."
msgstr "雖然原始資料和說明不會顯示在 GBIF.org 的網頁介面上，但它們可以通過下載提供給社群使用。輸入原始資料的說明時，請確保將其連結到原始活動或出現紀錄。例如，應將原始活動的 ID 或代碼輸入到 dwc:fieldNumber，並將原始出現觀察紀錄的 ID 或代碼輸入到 dwc:recordNumber。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:151
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "Publishing project data as a single dataset"
msgstr "將專案資料作為單一資料集發布"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:154
msgid "Data produced from a large sampling project should be published as a single dataset if possible. If you must publish multiple datasets, we encourage linking them using a common project identifier in the metadata."
msgstr "大型調查專案產生的資料應盡可能以單一資料集發布。如果必須發布多個資料集，建議在詮釋資料中使用共同的專案識別碼來連結這些資料集。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:155
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "Republishing occurrence data as sampling-event data"
msgstr "將出現紀錄資料重新發布為調查活動資料"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:159
msgid "Sampling events provide better documentation and benefit both the scientific community and policy makers (https://www.gbif.org/sampling-event-data[read more]).  We encourage strongly the republishing of occurrence data as sampling-event data when possible."
msgstr "調查活動資料能提供更好的紀錄文件，惠及科學界和政策制定者（https://www.gbif.org/sampling-event-data[閱讀更多]）。我們強烈建議在可能的情況下，將出現紀錄資料重新發布為調查活動資料。"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:161
msgid "In order to do so, you should create a new sampling-event dataset and send an email to GBIF's Help Desk (helpdesk@gbif.org). In this email, you should provide the UUIDs of both the occurrence dataset and the new dataset. We will then be able to link the first dataset to the newest one before de-indexing it thereby avoiding occurrence duplication and preserving citations."
msgstr "為此，您需要創建一個新的調查活動資料集，並將電子郵件發送至 GBIF 的服務台（helpdesk@gbif.org）。在郵件中，請提供出現紀錄資料集和新資料集的 UUID。我們將能夠在取消索引前，將第一個資料集與最新資料集連結，以避免資料重複並保留引用。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:162
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "Modelling continuous monitoring of live individuals"
msgstr "對活體個體的持續監測建模"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:165
msgid "If your dataset contains continuous monitoring of live individuals, such as bird tracking data, you can use dwc:organismID to store the ID of the individual being tracked. In addition to that, you should represent each individual being tracked as a single event."
msgstr "如果資料集中包含活體個體的持續監測（例如鳥類追蹤資料），可以使用 dwc:organismID 來存儲被追蹤個體的 ID。此外，應將每個被追蹤的個體表示為一個單獨的活動。"

#.  TODO: Provide a recommendation on how to model continuous monitoring of live individuals, such as bird tracking data by using dwc:organismID to store the ID of the individual being tracked and by using a single event for representing each individual being tracked (with associated occurrences where it was recorded).
#. type: Title ==
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:168
#, no-wrap
msgid "Continuous data quality improvement"
msgstr "資料品質的持續改進"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:170
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "Managing issues related to the dataset"
msgstr "管理資料集相關的問題"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:173
msgid "If possible, we recommend tracking all the issues related to a given dataset using an issue management system such as the one provided by GitHub."
msgstr "如可能，建議使用問題管理系統（例如 GitHub 提供的系統）來追蹤與資料集相關的所有問題。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:174
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:75
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sharing scripts and programs used to produce or clean the dataset"
msgstr "分享生成或清理資料集所用的腳本與程式"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:177
msgid "Ideally, custom scripts and programs used to transform data should be made publicly available on GitHub. Other publishers will benefit from accessing these scripts along with detailed instructions on how to use them."
msgstr "理想情況下，用於轉換資料的自定義腳本與程式應在 GitHub 上公開。其他發布者可從這些腳本以及詳細的使用說明中受益。"

#. type: Title ==
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:178
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "Describing sampling-event data in dataset metadata"
msgstr "在資料集詮釋資料中描述調查活動資料"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:181
msgid "Publishers should document their dataset as much as possible with a particular emphasis on sampling methodologies."
msgstr "發布者應盡可能詳細記錄資料集，尤其是調查方法。"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:184
msgid "Besides the https://www.gbif.org/data-quality-requirements-sampling-events[mandatory requirements], the metadata should include information about the extent of study, the sampling methods, the quality control and limitations of the study.  Although information about fieldwork can be part of the data content, you may describe the sampling location and conditions in the metadata as well."
msgstr "除了https://www.gbif.org/data-quality-requirements-sampling-events[強制要求的部分]，詮釋資料應包括關於研究範圍、調查方法、品質控制和研究限制的資訊。雖然田野工作資訊可以作為資料內容的一部分，您也可以在詮釋資料中描述調查位置和條件。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:185
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Linking related datasets"
msgstr "連結相關資料集"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:188
msgid "Some datasets may come from the same research project or may be related in certain context. The current recommendation is to link them using a project identifier."
msgstr "某些資料集可能來自同一研究專案，或者在某些情境下相關。目前的建議是使用專案識別碼將它們連結起來。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:189
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "Listing related research"
msgstr "列出相關研究"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:192
msgid "You can make your dataset easier to interpret by including links to related published works such as journal articles, project notes, thesis, etc,. in the bibliographic citation or in the external link part of the metadata."
msgstr "您可以在詮釋資料的書目引用部分或外部連結部分，加入相關已發布的作品（例如期刊文章、專案筆記、論文等）的連結，以便讓資料集更容易解讀。"

#. type: Title ==
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:193
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "Examples"
msgstr "範例"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:196
msgid "Following are some examples of typical sampling-event data sets. In each case, the key fields in the Event core and Occurrence extension are provided. For some examples, additional extensions such as Relevé and measurement-or-fact are also included."
msgstr "以下是一些典型調查活動資料集的範例。在每個案例中，均提供了調查活動核心集和物種出現紀錄延伸資料集中的關鍵欄位。某些範例還包含其他延伸資料集，例如樣區紀錄（Relevé）和“測量與事實”（Measurement-or-Fact）。"

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:197
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-planned-additions.adoc:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "Freshwater invertebrate survey"
msgstr "淡水無脊椎動物調查"

#. type: Plain text
